main event: A civilian reported observing a small whitish object resembling a star in flight for 1 minute and 20 seconds on 25 August 1965 in Washington Township, Ohio.
interesting points: The object was reported to have visual characteristics of a satellite observation., The object appeared to fade away at the end of the observation., The object was described as looking like a bright star but slightly brighter., The observer checked the ECHO and PEGASUS satellite schedules, which came back negative., The sighting was categorized and concluded as a satellite.
